#Text=The magistrates of Portsmouth have signified to the parish officers, that they will not in future sign any rate for the relief of the poor, until a list has been furnished to them of aU defaulters on former rates, being determined to assist the overseers by enforcing the payment of the several rales, as well as to scrutinize the expenditure of the money when raised.
